parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy

the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the active center differential pump can cause corrosion to the differential at an accelerated rate, leading to a hazardous situation that could damage property or cause injury or death.
symptoms: No specific symptoms mentioned
but the failure can cause corrosion to the differential.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing belt area can cause the engine to break down, leading to a hazardous situation that could damage property or cause injury or death.
symptoms: Grinding/scraping noise from the timing belt area
noise present at idle and upon cold start-ups.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a hazardous situation that could damage property or cause injury or death.
symptoms: Transmission grinds
transmission fails to shift gears
transmission slips.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Timing Belt and Idler Pulley Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing belt and idler pulley can cause catastrophic engine failure, leading to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Abnormal engine noises audible within the cabin
such as a washing machine or grinding sound
typically present when the engine is idling or during cold start-ups. The noise may disappear after 15 minutes of driving but can reappear later.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the rear subframe can cause the rear axle and suspension to detach from the body, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Significant corrosion perforation on the rear subframe
rust on the area where the rear axle and suspension mounts to the body
concern about the rear subframe assembly/control arms detaching due to rust.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the spring seat can cause the spring to translate and come into contact with the tire, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Broken spring seat at the weld joint to the shock tube
spring rubbing against the tire
extensive spring damage.
